{
  "stem": "8784.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he maybe was also naive somewhat, not knowing that if he points out children that the SS guards, in fact, could do away with the children very easily.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So all this has played a role, but the best part is that the SS guards did not recognize Oskar Schindler as an important individual.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they yelled back to him to keep what they delivered.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And at that, the SS guards left, and we stayed to, at the Oskar Schindler enamel works factory, as it was known at that time, Emalia.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we stayed as workers, as slave laborers.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't know of any other way-- there were no compensations for the workers, for us.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were simply ordered to stay there and work, and we worked.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And what is meant from now on is that I, together with the group of the 100, would be leaving the ghetto for a shift, whether it was a day shift or a night shift.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We would leave from the ghetto under the escorts of the German SS guards.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We would leave the ghetto and march daily to the factory of Oskar Schindler and work in that factory.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Food was in much better supply.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Somehow Schindler had some food on the premises in the factory.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So we were fed somewhat better than I would have been fed in the ghetto itself.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But my whole family of, of three brothers, two sisters, parents, remained in the ghetto, and I would walk out daily.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "My brother and sister and father were occasionally also rounded up and taken out of the ghetto and delivered back to the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But they were rounded up for work and, and would be returned.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "After either the same day or the next day, they would be returned to the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
